fields.title: Inglourious Basterds
fields.review: [Inglourious Basterds] is quintessentially Tarantino and a masterpiece that will be considered a classic fifty years from now.

fields.title: Dune
fields.review: From its opening shot to the final fade, I found myself enraptured and transported.

fields.title: Ngeri-Ngeri Sedap
fields.review: The real story about Bataknese life when they take care about their children. A lot of sorrow and tear in every event. Even if you from another culture, you can still cry while watching it.

fields.title: Gifted
fields.review: A very good watch, especially for the acting and the direction. Loved the chemistry between Chris Evans and Mckenna Grace.

fields.title: Good Will Hunting
fields.review: Its central performances are phenomenal and its inevitable emotional release is truly powerful.

fields.title: Jakarta Maghrib
fields.review: Salman Aristo memberi kritikan terhadap kondisi perfilman Indonesia yang memprihatinkan. Paling jelas digambarkan dalam segmen terakhir, Jalan Pintas, yang berisi keluhan tentang perfilman lokal yang dipenuhi dengan genre horror seks serta bagaimana perjuangan para filmmaker yang sedang merintis karir dalam menghadapi cibiran masyarakat yang menganggap bahwa pekerjaan mereka adalah sesuatu yang sia - sia dan tak ada artinya.

fields.title: fiksi
fields.review: Film ini berkisah mengenai kondisi kejiwaan seorang anak yang mengalami gejala traumatis serta terlalu dikungkung dalam kemewahan semu yang sepi.

fields.title: The Lost City
fields.review: A Mess of a Weak Plot and Little Chemistry

fields.title: Memories Of Murder
fields.review: A Gritty Murder Mystery with Political and Social Overtones. A Masterpiece that you cannot miss

fields.title: 500 Days Of Summer
fields.review: A love story deftly built on unrequited love.
